-- Russian Banks’ Capital Ratio Slides to 14.7%, Interfax Reports
-- B y   J a c k   J o r d a n
-- 2012-02-21T16:02:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-21/russian-banks-capital-ratio-slides-to-14-7-interfax-reports.html
Russian lenders’ average capital
adequacy ratio slid to 14.7 percent according to the latest
available data, Interfax reported, citing central bank Deputy
Chairman Mikhail Sukhov.  The regulator sees “nothing tragic happening now or in the
future” with capital levels in the banking industry, Sukhov was
cited as saying by the news service.  To contact the reporter on this story:
